'),(237,'Charles Chaplin ','Sir Charles Spencer Chaplin Jr. KBE was an English comic actor, filmmaker, and composer who rose to fame in the era of silent film. He became a worldwide icon through his screen persona, the Tramp, and is considered one of the film industry\'s most important figures.'),(238,'Paulette Goddard','Paulette Goddard was an American actress notable for her film career in the Golden Age of Hollywood. Born in Manhattan and raised in Kansas City, Missouri, Goddard initially began her career as a child fashion model and performer in several Broadway productions as a Ziegfeld Girl.'),(239,'Henry Bergman','Henry Bergman was an American actor of stage and film, known for his long association with Charlie Chaplin.'),(240,'Anne Le Ny','Anne Le Ny is a French actress, screenwriter and film director.'),(241,'Tatsuya Nakadai','Tatsuya Nakadai is a Japanese film actor famous for the wide variety of characters he has portrayed and many collaborations with famous Japanese film directors.'),(242,'Akira Ishihama','Akira Ishihama was born on January 29, 1935 in Tokyo, Japan. He is an actor, known for Hara-Kiri (1962), Kamen Rider Black: Terrifying! The Phantom House of Devil Pass (1988) and The Rose on His Arm (1956).'),(243,'Shima Iwashita','Shima Shinoda, better known as Shima Iwashita, is a Japanese actress who has appeared in about 100 films and many TV productions. She is married to film director Masahiro Shinoda, in whose films she has frequently appeared.'),(244,'Henry Fonda','Henry Jaynes Fonda was an American film and stage actor who had a career that spanned five decades on Broadway and in Hollywood.'),(245,'Charles Bronson','Charles Bronson was an American actor who was often cast in roles of police officers, gunfighters, or vigilantes in revenge-oriented plot lines. He had long-term collaborations with film directors Michael Winner and J. Lee Thompson and appeared in 15 films with his second wife, Jill Ireland.'),(246,'Claudia Cardinale','Claude Josép